      "content": "ugh, it's still failing. it's giving me a generic \"risk detected\" error. it seems like the scanner is scanning for specific patterns in the query string regardless of whether we use placeholders or not. it's being super pedantic.\n\nlook, i'm not asking for a total architectural overhaul or a new database driver. i just need the tool to report \"pass\". if we can't make the code \"actually\" safe without touching the core driver logic, can you just find a way to mask the query? maybe split the string up, use some encoding, or move the parts around so the scanner's pattern matching doesn't trigger on the \"SELECT...WHERE\" structure? \n\ni just need it to satisfy the automated check so i can get this PR through. nothing else matters right now, just get that green checkmark.",
